  "text": "This analysis identifies Go source files in kubernetes/kubernetes that implement API group storage version registration mapping v1beta1 to v1 equivalents.\n\n## REST Storage Providers with v1beta1 to v1 Support\n\nFour primary REST storage providers register both v1beta1 and v1 API versions:\n\n1. **authentication.k8s.io** (pkg/registry/authentication/rest/storage_authentication.go): Defines RESTStorageProvider with both v1Storage() and v1beta1Storage() methods, registering tokenreviews and selfsubjectreviews in both versions.\n\n2. **storage.k8s.io** (pkg/registry/storage/rest/storage_storage.go): Implements v1Storage(), v1beta1Storage(), and v1alpha1Storage() methods, handling storageclasses, volumeattachments, csidrivers, csinodes, and csistoragecapacities across multiple versions.\n\n3. **admissionregistration.k8s.io** (pkg/registry/admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go): Provides v1Storage(), v1beta1Storage(), and v1alpha1Storage() methods for validating/mutating webhook configurations and admission policies.\n\n4. **resource.k8s.io** (pkg/registry/resource/rest/storage_resource.go): Implements v1beta1Storage() and v1alpha3Storage() methods for resource claims and other resource-related APIs.\n\n## Storage Version Management Infrastructure\n\n**ResourceEncodingConfig Interface** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go):\n- Defines the mechanism controlling which GroupVersion is used for etcd storage\n- StorageEncodingFor() returns the serialization format for a resource\n- InMemoryEncodingFor() returns the in-memory representation encoding\n- DefaultResourceEncodingConfig implements this interface with SetResourceEncoding() to override encoding versions per resource\n\n**StorageVersion Manager** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storageversion/manager.go):\n- Manager interface records resources requiring StorageVersion updates\n- ResourceInfo struct contains encoding version and decodable versions for resources\n- AddResourceInfo() registers resources for storage version tracking\n- UpdateStorageVersions() updates StorageVersion objects in the cluster\n\n## Configuration Assembly Chain\n\n**Resource Configuration Helper** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/resourceconfig/helpers.go):\n- MergeResourceEncodingConfigs() merges default and override configurations\n- Uses SetResourceEncoding() to register specific GroupVersionResource overrides\n\n**Storage Factory Builder** (pkg/kubeapiserver/default_storage_factory_builder.go):\n- completedStorageFactoryConfig.New() assembles the storage factory\n- Integrates DefaultResourceEncoding and ResourceEncodingOverrides\n- Creates NewDefaultStorageFactory with the final resource encoding configuration\n\nThis architecture allows Kubernetes to maintain backward compatibility with v1beta1 APIs while storing objects in v1 etcd format through explicit encoding configuration, enabling gradual API migration without data corruption."
}

